This is a 4 pin Weather Pack Connector 'tower' housing. To help prevent confusion, female terminals are used with 'Tower housings' and and male terminals are used with 'Shroud housings'. Crimping and assembly is the same no matter if you're using a tower or shroud, or a male/female terminal. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Assemble-Weather-Pack-Connectors-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Assemble-Weather-Pack-Connectors-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/85/Assemble-Weather-Pack-Connectors-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Assemble-Weather-Pack-Connectors-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
